"To my great despair I noticed recently that the site was unfortunately no longer available — Im not really sure what happen. So as an hommage to the Kern King with special thanks to my friend Seb for finding the source I decided to resuscitate the useful guide here in our Journal.

Heres how it works:
First complete the spacing of your font in progress but before adding kerning copy the Kern King text from this page paste it into the font software of your choice Glyphs Robofont FontLabetc... look at the words in lowercase then as all caps and see how they set. Make a list of all the problem pairs: those that are too far apart and those that are too close together. Make corrections to spacing and add kerning. Check again. Repeat process until kerning seems perfect.

Kern King Part 1: Lowercase kern text
